Pynguin is a python-based turtle graphics application.
It combines an editor, interactive interpreter, and
graphics display area.

http://pynguin.googlecode.com/


INSTALLATION:
    First, make sure the dependencies are installed, then follow
    the instructions in the appropriate section below:

    Ubuntu Linux:
        There is experimental support for installing from a .deb
        distribution. The .deb was produced on Ubuntu 11.04.
        Attempting to install it on other versions may or may not
        work. Please report success or failure either way!

    Others:
        Unpack the archive, then run setup from a command line:

        python setup.py install


        It is also possible to run the application directly from
        the unpacked archive.


DEPENDENCIES:
    python:
        http://python.org/
            (tested with python-2.7.1)

    pyqt4:
        http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/pyqt/
            (tested with pyqt-4.8.3)

    pygments (optional):
        http://pygments.org/
            (tested with 1.3.1)


RUNNING:
    Run the program from the command prompt like this:

        ./pynguin

    or

        python pynguin


    For a quick introduction, choose welcome.pyn
        from the File->Examples menu

    More information is available on the wiki here:
        http://code.google.com/p/pynguin/wiki/GettingStarted


DEVELOPMENT:
    Pynguin is released under GPLv3.

    please report any problems here:
        http://code.google.com/p/pynguin/issues/list
